1 can access essential weekend and evening care services through adult
2 day centers and residential care facilities equipped to meet the
3 unique needs of seniors. The ultimate goal is to reduce caregiver
4 burnout, support working families, and improve the well-being of
5 both seniors and their caregivers by offering flexible care options.
6 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.3 of Title 63, unless there
8 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 For purposes of this act:
10 1. "Adult day center" means a licensed facility providing
11 social, health-related, or personal care services in a protective
12 setting during the day;
13 2. "Respite care" means temporary relief for primary caregivers
14 of seniors, providing short-term care for seniors in appropriate
15 settings;
16 3. "Residential care facility" means a facility licensed to
17 provide care services to seniors who do not require twenty-four-hour
18 nursing care but need assistance with daily living activities;
19 4. "Respite waiver" refers to financial assistance provided to
20 eligible caregivers, ensuring access to respite care services at no
21 or reduced cost; and
22 5. "Voucher" means a payment issued to caregivers allowing them
23 to obtain respite care services from participating care providers.
