1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.4 of Title 63, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The Department of Human Services (DHS) is hereby authorized
5 to establish and administer pilot programs for the provision of
6 respite care vouchers or respite waivers to caregivers of seniors
7 limited to designated counties, and within the designated counties,
8 qualified facilities may opt into the pilot program.
9 B. The pilot programs shall:
10 1. Provide financial assistance in the form of vouchers or
11 waivers for caregivers of seniors, enabling them to access care
12 services outside traditional hours, including weekend and evening
13 care;
14 2. Prioritize caregivers who are employed in evening-hour or
15 nontraditional work schedules, ensuring they have access to services
16 when needed most; and
17 3. Facilitate the participation of adult day centers,
18 residential care facilities, and other licensed providers equipped
19 to deliver care for seniors with various health and personal needs.
20 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.5 of Title 63, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 A. To qualify for participation in the respite care pilot
24 programs, applicants shall:
Req. No. 12212 Page 3

1 1. Be primary caregivers of seniors aged sixty-five (65) years
2 or older;
3 2. Demonstrate employment in evening-hour jobs or
4 nontraditional work schedules where traditional caregiving services
5 are not sufficient; and
6 3. Provide documentation demonstrating financial need for
7 respite care assistance, as determined by the Department of Human
8 Services (DHS).
9 B. Applications for respite care vouchers or waivers shall be
10 made to (DHS), which will evaluate and approve applicants based on
11 established criteria.
12 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.6 of Title 63, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. Eligible providers for respite care services under this act
16 shall include:
17 1. Licensed adult day centers and residential care facilities;
18 and
19 2. Other licensed care agencies equipped to meet the unique
20 needs of seniors.
21 B. Providers shall be reimbursed by the state for services
22 rendered under the voucher or waiver programs, based on rates
23 established by the Department of Human Services (DHS).
