1 SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.7 of Title 63, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. The respite care pilot programs established by this act
5 shall be funded through multiple sources, including but not limited
6 to:
7 1. Grants from federal, state, or private sources;
8 2. Public-private partnerships designed to support caregiving
9 and senior care; and
10 3. Allocated state funds, subject to legislative
11 appropriations.
12 B. The Department of Human Services (DHS) is authorized to seek
13 and apply for available federal and state funding to support the
14 pilot programs, including funds under the Medicaid program and other
15 relevant federal initiatives.
16 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3119.8 of Title 63, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Department of Human Services (DHS) shall conduct an
20 annual review and report to the Legislature on the effectiveness of
21 the respite care pilot programs, including:
22 1. The number of caregivers served by the programs;
23 2. Data on the utilization of care services during
24 nontraditional hours; and
